items.name: Simplicity Anime
items.description:
Simplicity Anime - Beta 1 is up!

Simplicity Anime objective is to be able to do good art with little promptingüòÖ
The model is very easy to use and is perfect for people who do not want to bother with a prompt.

I also have a boosty page where you can support me and see a lot of life hacks and tips on Stable Diffusion <3, I would really appreciate it: https://boosty.to/simplicity

‚¨áRead the info below to get the same quality imagesüôè

////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////

Recommended Settings - VAE built into the model

  • Clip skip: 2

  • Hires. fix: R-ESRGAN 4x+ Anime6B / Upscale by: 1.5+ / Hires steps: 8 / Denoising strength: 0.4

  • Adetailer: face_yolov8n

  • Sampler: DPM++ 2M Karras

  • CFG: 7 / Steps : 22+

  • It works best on these resolution dimensions:

    • 512x512

    • 512x768

    • 768x512

////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////

Why is my image different from yours?

  • Use prompts that match the danbooru tag

    • Keywords like Realistic, HDR, and others sometimes force changes to the characteristics of the model

    • Tag auto complete extension

  • Use Neg only when necessary

  • A lot of negative embedding is not always the answer

  • If you're having trouble with your character's face (especially the eyes), set the Upscale to 2 or higher. If you don't have enough VRAM, Adetailer is an alternative

  • Different samplers will produce different results

  • I can't give you a solution to the error or any technical help

////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////

Do you like my work? check out my profile and see what else!

Take a look at my Boosty and you can do exactly the same! üòâ

////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////

Thank you for downloading!
Please leave a image with comment if you like it, I would love to see.

items.name: Christopher Walken
items.description:
This is the young Chris, old Chris will be uploaded separately.

Be nice, have fun!

Christopher Walken (born Ronald Walken; March 31, 1943) is an American actor. Prolific in film, television, and on stage, Walken is the recipient of numerous accolades. He has earned an Academy Award, a BAFTA Award, a Screen Actors Guild Award, as well as nominations for two Primetime Emmy Awards and two Tony Awards. His films have grossed more than $1.6 billion in the United States alone.[1]

Walken has appeared in supporting roles in films such as The Anderson Tapes (1971), Next Stop, Greenwich Village (1976), Roseland (1977) and Annie Hall (1977), before coming to wider attention as the troubled Vietnam War veteran Nick Chevotarevich in The Deer Hunter (1978). His performance earned him an Academy Award for Best Supporting Actor. He was nominated for the same award for portraying con artist Frank Abagnale's father in Steven Spielberg's Catch Me If You Can (2002).

Since his breakthrough, Walken has appeared in films in various genres, both in lead and supporting roles.[2] These include The Dogs of War (1980), The Dead Zone (1983), A View to a Kill (1985), At Close Range (1986), Biloxi Blues (1988), King of New York (1990), The Comfort of Strangers (1990), Batman Returns (1992), True Romance (1993), Pulp Fiction (1994), Suicide Kings (1997), Sleepy Hollow (1999), Man on Fire (2004), Wedding Crashers (2005), Hairspray (2007), Seven Psychopaths (2012), A Late Quartet (2012), the first three Prophecy films, and Percy (2020). He has also provided voice work for the animated films Antz (1998) and The Jungle Book (2016).

On television, Walken has appeared in films such as Who Am I This Time? (1982), and Sarah, Plain and Tall (1991), for which he received a Primetime Emmy Award nomination. More recently, he has starred in television series The Outlaws (2021-), and Severance (2022-), the latter of which earned him a Primetime Emmy Award for Outstanding Supporting Actor in a Drama Series nomination. He is a popular guest-host of Saturday Night Live, hosting seven times. His most notable roles on the show include record producer Bruce Dickinson in the "More Cowbell" sketch, the disgraced Confederate officer Colonel Angus, and multiple appearances as an aging, unsuccessful lothario in the Continental sketch.

As a stage actor, Walken starred with Irene Worth in a 1975 Broadway revival of ‚ÄúSweet Bird of Youth.‚Äù Walken has played the lead in the Shakespeare plays Hamlet, Macbeth, Romeo and Juliet, and Coriolanus. His performance in the original rendition of James Joyce's The Dead (2000), earned him a Tony Award for Best Actor in a Musical nomination. He was nominated for the Tony Award for Best Actor in a Play for his role in Martin McDonagh's A Behanding in Spokane (2010). He also wrote and played the lead role in the 1995 play Him, about his idol Elvis Presley.[3]

This large model is created to pursue realism, and it excels in drawing characters, especially various young ladies, especially Asian women.

Due to the consideration that the uncontrollability of blending is relatively large, in order to pursue the best realism, I planned not to blend this large model with any other existing large models when creating it, but continuously adding a large number of real ultra-high-definition photos and concepts for learning.

I believe that this will eventually form a very special realistic large model.

Many of the high-definition photo materials that have been added are paid for, and have been accumulated over a long period of time. For this, I specifically bought a 4090 card (laughs).

This is very hard work. The first version was chosen from hundreds of versions, and before making this version, more than a dozen versions have already been abandoned by me.

I will keep updating, adding more concepts to make this model richer and richer.

Below is a comparison of images generated using the same keywords with the currently most popular several realistic large models without using plugins. Please refer to it.

Many keywords are taken directly from the example images of these large models.

I will keep updating this model. Every time I add several new concepts, I might update it.

Usage:

  1. VAE: Personal preference. Try those suitable for realism. I used 84000 in the example.

  2. Clip: I am more accustomed to using 2.

  3. Iteration steps: 30-50, just don‚Äôt set it too low.

  4. Sampling method: Many new sampling methods are emerging, it is recommended to try more.

  5. It is recommended not to turn on facial repair.

  6. It is recommended to turn on high-definition repair.

  7. Don't set the repainting range too high, it is recommended to be between 0.25-0.55, the magnification is recommended to be set to 2. If the memory is not enough, you can turn on Tiled VAE, or set it to 1.5.

  8. Prompt word guidance coefficient: Between 5-12. 7, 7.5, 8 are three good starting points.

  9. It is not recommended to turn on face repair unless you are pursuing a personalized face shape. This large model will not always produce the same face shape because the material photos are different.

  10. To pursue simplicity and ease of use, there are no specific prompt words, prompt words from various real series models are applicable.

  11. Good light and shadow effects can appear without adding light and shadow LORA, please try more.

items.description:
Ginrummy Character LoRA!

Making models can be time consuming and expensive. If you like what I do consider commissioning a LoRA or buying me a borgarüçî!

This is a small side-character from the series One Piece! Despite being a non-nami-clone favorite, this character has a super small amount of love in the way of anime screen time and fan art. I was able to find 9 good shots before having to go synthetic.

That being said, this is a WIP and I assume after many of you make art and post some here i can retrain and hopefully provide even better results!

This LoRA is very good with nsfw prompts! The trigger word is ginrummyv1 and you will want to use prompts like horns, blue eyes, red lips, hoop earrings to get her general style. Blue Pauldrons would possibly make her main outfit show up better.
I reccommend using hires fix as well.

This is Tien's eternal companion, Chiaotzu.

I have a kofi if you want to support my work. I also take commissions, so if you are interested on a training, check that out. I also have a Pixiv where I upload pics from testing and tease the things I'm working on! Or go to my wife's Pixiv, she has sexy pics of my LoRAs and WIPs.

I tried to make it a little better, I added the outfit from Super, but for some reason the AI really struggles with his outfits. Some tags were changed so check the tags below or at the trigger words.

About the LoRA, his appereance is chaozu, black eyes, blush stickers,bald. That's it, sometimes it tries to make the single hair, but not on black if he's not wearing the hat. As always, I'll leave examples in the gallery, I didn't inpaint anything so there's always room for improvement. All the pictures are made with weight 1. The source is mostly old, so I recommend using hires with 0.3-0.5 denoise depending on the model, buuuuuut, at 0.5 sometimes it makes things that shouldn't be there, like double eyebrows, part of the things that I have to fix.

The outfits available are:

  • The Crane school one: green vest, yellow sleeves, black pants, black flats, black headwear, red pom pom \(clothes\),kanji

  • The Saiyan/Android saga: light blue tank top, black pants, black boots, red sash, green wristbands,black headwear, red pom pom \(clothes\)

  • The DB Super: black vest, light blue sleeves, light blue pants, black boots, black hat, red pom pom \(clothes\),kanji


If a part of the other outfit starts randomly showing just place it on negative and it should go away. Also, to get the DB/DBZ hat now, use black headwearand have black hatas negative.

items.name: Adriana Torrebejano
items.description:
Adriana Torrebejano is a Spanish actress mainly known for her roles in some TV shows from my country. She might not be world famous, but I think you'll agree her beauty deserves a spot at CivitAI. :)

This is a 250-step TI trained on a dataset of 15 images with these settings.

Appreciate my work? My TIs are free, but you can always buy me a coffee. :)

Curious about my work process? I have summarized it here.

Building a good prompt with my TIs

You're obviously free to experiment, but bear in mind that my TIs are trained with a more or less fixed phrasing, that normally starts with:

"photo of EMBEDDING_NAME, a woman"

So I recommend always starting your prompt like that and then building the rest of the prompt from there. For instance, "photo of beautiful (t0rrebe:0.99), a woman as a movie star, sweater off-shoulders, trousers, at a movie premiere gala, dark moody ambience (masterpiece:1.2) (photorealistic:1.2) (bokeh) (best quality) (detailed skin:1.2) (intricate details) (nighttime) (8k) (HDR) (cinematic lighting) (sharp focus), (looking at the camera:1.1), (closeup portrait:1.1)"

items.name: Sci-fi XL Style
items.description:
Introducing Sci-fi XL Style Model: An AI Model Inspired by StableDiffusion XL

The Sci-fi XL Style Model is a Lora model for SD 1.5 specifically developed to mimic the style and aesthetic of the popular image generation model, StableDiffusion XL. Trained over 16 epochs and 5.728 steps.

The dataset used to train the Sci-fi XL Style Model was carefully crafted to encompass a wide range of captivating sci-fi scenes, including futuristic cityscapes, alien landscapes, advanced technology, and other elements commonly associated with the genre. By extracting the most exceptional examples of sci-fi imagery generated by StableDiffusion XL 0.9 Beta, the dataset ensures that the model learns to replicate the captivating and otherworldly qualities that define sci-fi aesthetics.

items.name: BBC-Chan Style
items.description:
BBC-Chan inspired style LoRA

How to use
This is a test LoRA trained AOM2 instead of NAI which I normally use. The dataset consist of a older limited set of mainly "1girl" images from the artist. Things it's good at is pointy ears, dark-skin, kemonomimi, muscle, breasts, horns and the occasional feminine penis.

I recommend starting with a LoRA strength of 0.7 and increase from there if needed. I also suggest trying both Euler A and DPM++ 2M Karras samplers to see which one work best with your model. The former usually gives a more clean look while the latter a more drawlike style.
You can also try adding "3D" and/or "realistic" in negatives, especially if your model has some degree of realism mixed in.

Don't forget to review and upload your own images, it's always fun to see what you're creating!
Like my LoRAs and want more? Please consider a small tip towards my electricity bill and further training >.<

MISC
Trained on AOM2 at 512px with 60 images.
All images are raw txt2img upscaled without any helper embeddings.

items.name: Kakigori
items.description:
About the model:

My goal with this mix was to create a mostly 2d anime style model that responds well to varied prompts, including a relatively wide range of existing characters without the need of additional LoRAs. NSFW was not a focus for this model, but it can still do it. I have done little testing on LoRA compatibility with this model because I primarily use style LoRAs and this model already has the style that I wanted it to have.

I'd love to see what you create with this model!

Prompting:

Kakigori responds best to booru style prompting, although it can handle some natural language prompting.

Example prompt: 

kirisame marisa, blonde hair, side braid, waist apron, witch hat, hat bow, yellow eyes, superb, looking down, splashing in a stream, nature, outdoors

I find that a simple negative prompt without any negative embeddings has worked best for me.
Example negative prompt:

(Worst Quality, Low Quality:1.2), border, nsfw, skimpy, grayscale, multiple_girls, (watermark:1.2)

Recommended settings:

Clip skip: 2

Base Resolution: ~512x768 or 768x512

Hires. fix: 4x_fatal_Anime_500000K_G / Upscale by: 1.5+ / Denoising strength: 0.48

Adetailer: face_yolov8n

Sampler: DPM++ 2M Karras/DPM++ 2M SDE Karras

CFG: 7.5 / Steps : 20

Credits:

I would like to give thanks to the authors of the following models which were included in this merge. If you like my merge then I would encourage you to try these out as well.

AuroraONE by Luna

Toonyou - JP - Alpha 1 by Bradcatt

ExpMix_Line - V3 by Mods13

(VAE) kl-f8-anime2 by hakurei

Why baked VAE?:

Because I see too many people using models without the correct VAE too often, the impact to file size is tiny, and I don't expect this model to be great for training from anyways. You can still load whichever VAE you would like in WebUI and if you're more than welcome to prune the VAE yourself if you'd prefer that. The VAE I used is a customized version of kl-f8-anime2 with lower contrast than the official version. If you would like a copy of the VAE baked into this model you can get WD1-4-kl-f8-anime2-bless09 here.

This model may not be used on any paid generation services. You may not sell this model or any merges that contain it. This model is for personal/private use. Commercial use is not authorized.

You are more than welcome to include this model in merges as long as those merges adhere to the same license as this model. If you upload your merge all I ask is that you include a link to this model in the about section like I have done here.
